underlying_goal: To create a 4-page workshop paper from a specification, and when the first attempt was too short, to use a multi-agent process to critique the approach and generate a better plan.
friction_detail: Claude's first attempt at generating the paper from the plan resulted in a draft that was only 2.5 pages, significantly under the 4-page target.
primary_success: After the initial generated paper was too short, Claude successfully orchestrated a multi-agent critique (using Gemini, Codex, and a Plan agent) to analyze the failure and produce a much stronger, more detailed plan for the next attempt.
brief_summary: Claude created a LaTeX paper from a plan, but the result was too short (2.5 pages). The user then asked for a re-plan, which Claude executed by gathering critiques from three different AI agents and synthesizing their feedback into a new, more robust plan for expanding the paper.
